Comment[Let's pause and take a look.  Locally, W is advantageous -- after taking two B stones, W is thick and thus weakened the three B stones on the right.  Globally, however, B lived all the stones at the top side \(quite a bit of territory\), and B gains sente \(remember W played first\).  So B should be satisfied.]
